<subSubSection id="7C82B90DC6578D098B927AC884FD10E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3522239CD7EE4DE005A446F65260161C" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE4C7F00CA2948BEC8977711B73C2AE8" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Larger body length, usually between 9.5-14 mm; mandibles with four teeth (plus molar one); pronotum distinctively wider than long. elytra 3.3-3.6 times longer than wide, finely punctate; aedeagus very thin and distinctly hooked, internal sac sclerites shape variable.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
